ðŸ”¹ Regex Cheat Sheet
1. Basics

Symbol	Meaning
.	Any character except newline
\	Escape special character (e.g., \. matches .)
^	Start of string/line
$	End of string/line
|	OR (e.g., cat|dog)

2. Character Classes

Pattern	Meaning
[abc]	Match a, b, or c
[^abc]	NOT a, b, or c
[a-z]	Range (lowercase letters)
[A-Z]	Range (uppercase letters)
[0-9]	Digits
\d	Digit (same as [0-9])
\D	Not a digit
\w	Word character [A-Za-z0-9_]
\W	Not a word character
\s	Whitespace (space, tab, newline)
\S	Not whitespace

3. Quantifiers

Pattern	Meaning
*	0 or more
+	1 or more
?	0 or 1 (optional)
{n}	Exactly n
{n,}	n or more
{n,m}	Between n and m

4. Groups & Anchors

Pattern	Meaning
(abc)	Capturing group
(?:abc)	Non-capturing group
(?<name>abc)	Named capturing group
\1	Backreference to group 1
\b	Word boundary
\B	Not a word boundary

5. Assertions

Pattern	Meaning
(?=...)	Positive lookahead (must be followed by â€¦)
(?!...)	Negative lookahead (must NOT be followed by â€¦)
(?<=...)	Positive lookbehind (must be preceded by â€¦)
(?<!...)	Negative lookbehind

6. Common Examples

Regex	Matches
\d{3}-\d{2}-\d{4}	SSN format: 123-45-6789
\(\d{3}\) \d{3}-\d{4}	Phone number (123) 456-7890
[A-Za-z0-9._%+-]+@[A-Za-z0-9.-]+\.[A-Za-z]{2,}	Email
https?://[^\s/$.?#].[^\s]*	URL
^[A-Z][a-z]+$	Capitalized word
